cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a method for domain adaptation using adversarial learning. The focus is on learning categorical information from unlabeled target samples with the help of labeled source samples. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). However, given the emphasis on learning features and aligning them at the category level, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories.
